{"key":"processedPost-12678077","value":{"id":12678077,"first":12677143,"last":12692051,"when":1275585589,"utime":"06/03/10 08:19 PM","content":"It's probably not condensation.&nbsp; I suspect you're pumping in way too much moisture.&nbsp; If the air is already at 100%, it can't absorb any more, thus the extra moisture falls onto your substrate like rain.&nbsp; In my mini-greenhouses, I only use a coolmist, no ultrasonic, and the cool mist only runs for one minute on, five to six minutes off.&nbsp; This results in a humidity in the 90s.<br /><br />Be sure to have lots of holes and/or slits cut in the plastic to allow for fresh air to enter and exit.<br /><br />Calibrate your hygrometer by wrapping it up in a damp towel for an hour to make sure it reads 99%.<br />RR","title":"Re: Getting rid of heavy condensation."}}